{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:48:13.347788+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I've reviewed the repository's README, `package.json`, and `.env` template. Here's a summary of the three stages:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Installation\n\nScaffold a new project from this CRA (Create React App) template using **npm** or **Yarn**:\n\n```bash\n# npm\nnpx create-react-app your-project-name --template firebase-starter\n\n# yarn\nyarn create react-app your-project-name --template firebase-starter\n```\n\nThis will create a new React app pre-wired with React Router, Material UI, Firebase Auth (Google sign-in), and GitHub Pages deployment support.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Configuration (Firebase + Google Sign-In)\n\n### a) Set up your Firebase project\n\n1. Go to the [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com/), click **Add project**, and follow the wizard.\n2. Register a **Web app** (click the web icon `</>`). Firebase will give you an SDK config with keys like `apiKey`, `authDomain`, `projectId`, etc.\n\n### b) Populate the `.env` file\n\nIn the project root, replace the placeholder values in `.env` with your real Firebase credentials:\n\n```\nREACT_APP_FirebaseApiKey=<your-api-key>\nREACT_APP_FirebaseAuthDomain=<your-auth-domain>\nREACT_APP_FirebaseProjectId=<your-project-id>\nREACT_APP_FirebaseStorageBucket=<your-storage-bucket>\nREACT_APP_FirebaseMessagingSenderId=<your-sender-id>\nREACT_APP_FirebaseAppId=<your-app-id>\n```\n\n### c) Enable Google sign-in\n\n1. In the Firebase Console, navigate to **Authentication → Get Started**.\n2. Under the **Sign-in method** tab, select **Google**, toggle **Enable**, and click **Save**.\n\n### d) (Optional) Add new routes/screens\n\n1. Create a component in `src/screens/`.\n2. Add a route entry in `src/config/routes.js`:\n   ```js\n   {\n       path: \"/your-route\",\n       component: YourScreenComponent,\n       name: \"Screen Name\",\n       protected: false,  // true = requires authentication\n   }\n   ```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Deploy to GitHub Pages\n\n1. **Add your GitHub Pages domain** (`your-username.github.io`) to the **OAuth redirect domains** list in the Firebase Console → Authentication → Sign-in method tab.\n\n2. **Update `homepage` in `package.json`** to match your deployment URL:\n   ```json\n   \"homepage\": \"http://your-github-username.github.io/your-repo-name\"\n   ```\n\n3. **(Optional) Test the production build locally:**\n   ```bash\n   # Temporarily set \"homepage\": \"/\" in package.json, then:\n   npm i -g serve\n   npm run build-and-serve\n   ```\n\n4. **Deploy:**\n   ```bash\n   npm run deploy\n   ```\n   Under the hood, this runs `npm run build` (the `predeploy` script) and then `gh-pages -d build`, which pushes the production build to a `gh-pages` branch. A `404.html` file in `public/` handles SPA routing so client-side routes work correctly on GitHub Pages.\n\n---\n\n**Key dependencies that make this work:** `firebase` + `react-firebase-hooks` (auth), `react-router-dom` (routing), `@mui/material` (UI), and `gh-pages` (deployment).", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 759, "prompt_tokens": 9047, "total_tokens": 9806, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 33, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8832, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0007856502, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001253202, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00066033}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780962478-qsRw6uWtrXA9tdV2ayOV", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9a2-c7f6-7452-a1f5-61ba2ca28dee-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": 